cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the generation and evaluation of terrains in computer graphics. It also involves the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also uses quantitative evaluation based on localized geomorphology-based landform features, which could fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of perceptual studies and metrics also suggests a possible fit with the Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
